<subSubSection pageId="63" pageNumber="2845" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="63.[120,762,818,1476]" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[121,400,897,921]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lentilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="hilgardii">
<emphasis box="[121,400,897,921]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845">Lentilactobacillus hilgardii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(hil.gar’di.i. N.L. gen. n. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Zheng &amp; Wittouck &amp; Salvetti &amp; Franz &amp; Harris &amp; Mattarelli &amp; O’Toole &amp; Pot &amp; Vandamme &amp; Walter &amp; Watanabe &amp; Wuyts &amp; Felis &amp; Gänzle &amp; Lebeer" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[672,760,897,921]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lentilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="hilgardii">
<emphasis box="[672,760,897,921]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845">hilgardii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of Hilgard, named after E.W. Hilgard, a pioneer of enology in the State of 
<collectingRegion box="[275,385,959,983]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845">California</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[395,450,959,983]" name="United States of America" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845">USA</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="63" pageNumber="2845" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="63.[120,762,818,1476]" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845">
Basonym: 
<taxonomicName authority="Douglas and Cruess 1936" authorityName="Douglas and Cruess" authorityYear="1936" box="[235,756,1005,1029]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lactobacillus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="hilgardii">
<emphasis box="[235,468,1005,1029]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845">Lactobacillus hilgardii</emphasis>
Douglas and Cruess 1936
</taxonomicName>
, 115 (Approved Lists); the species was initially described in 1936; the description was emended in 1949 after the original 
<typeStatus box="[121,167,1098,1122]" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845">type</typeStatus>
strain was lost [
<bibRefCitation author="Douglas HC &amp; Cruess W." box="[336,379,1098,1122]" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845" pagination="113 - 119" refId="ref74288" refString="330. Douglas HC, Cruess W. A Lactobacillus from California wine: Lactobacillus hilgardii. J Food Sci 1936; 1: 113 - 119." type="journal article" year="1936">330</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vaughn RH &amp; Douglas HC &amp; Fornachon JCM" box="[390,431,1098,1122]" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845" pagination="133 - 139" refId="ref74316" refString="331. Vaughn RH, Douglas HC, Fornachon JCM. The taxonomy of Lactobacillus hilgardii and related heterofermentative lactobacilli. Hilgardia 1949; 19: 133 - 139." type="journal article" year="1949">331</bibRefCitation>
]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="63" pageNumber="2845" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="63.[120,762,818,1476]" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845">
Strains grow optimally between pH 4.5 and 5.5 and in the range of 15 to 40 °C [
<bibRefCitation author="Douglas HC &amp; Cruess W." box="[349,392,1175,1199]" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845" pagination="113 - 119" refId="ref74288" refString="330. Douglas HC, Cruess W. A Lactobacillus from California wine: Lactobacillus hilgardii. J Food Sci 1936; 1: 113 - 119." type="journal article" year="1936">330</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vaughn RH &amp; Douglas HC &amp; Fornachon JCM" box="[403,446,1175,1199]" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845" pagination="133 - 139" refId="ref74316" refString="331. Vaughn RH, Douglas HC, Fornachon JCM. The taxonomy of Lactobacillus hilgardii and related heterofermentative lactobacilli. Hilgardia 1949; 19: 133 - 139." type="journal article" year="1949">331</bibRefCitation>
]. The genome size of the 
<typeStatus box="[716,762,1175,1199]" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845">type</typeStatus>
strain is 2.60 Mbp. The mol% G+C content of DNA is 39.6.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="63.[120,762,818,1476]" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845">Isolated from spoiled wine, kefir grains, mezcal fermentations and silage.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
